Package: friedman
Title: Nonparametric Repeated Measures Analysis via Friedman's Test
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Ian", "Alloway",
    email = "ianalloway@usf.edu",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Provides a complete workflow for Friedman's nonparametric
    two-way analysis of variance by ranks. Includes the core test,
    Kendall's W effect size, pairwise post-hoc comparisons via the
    Nemenyi test, ggplot2-based visualizations, and a report generator
    for publication-ready output. Designed for researchers analyzing
    repeated-measures data that violates normality assumptions.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    tidyr,
    broom,
    PMCMRplus
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/ianalloway/friedman
BugReports: https://github.com/ianalloway/friedman/issues
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
